WARRI – Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie, a frontline Delta State House of Assembly aspirant from Ughelli South Constituency has received a Prestigious award of Youth Ambassador of the year 2021 from Uhurie United Union, aka Tripple U. Chief Francis Vevakpor, the National Coordinator of Uhurie United Union in his speech shortly before the presentation of the plaque and the certificate stated that the Union collectively decided to bestow the honour on Hon. Dr Gordons Okomitie due to his contributions to Youth development, engagement and empowerment through his capacity-building Prógràmmes organized periodically to add value and improve the living status of youth in Uhurie communities, the Ughievwen Kingdom in particular and Urhobo land in general. Chief Francis Vivakpor while promisingthe Union’s total support towards Hon Gordons Okomitie House of Assembly ambition said:“The awardee has embarked on Agricultural Projects which are very strategic in boosting thefood production capacity of Ughelli South with a positive multiplier effect of mass employment for youths cutting across party affiliations.” The Uhurie United Union boss remarked in his statement that the Group is quite impressed with what Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie is doing for the people already, adding that if such a man is given the opportunity to represent Ughelli South in the Delta State House of Assembly, the Constituency can be sure of qualitative representation and abundant dividends of democracy because he is tested and trusted. Speaking further, he explained that it is the turn of the Uhurie people to Produce the candidate for the Ughelli South Constituency, and the best man for the post is Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie, a frontline grass-root Politician who has made himself available to serve thepeople as their Lawmaker come 2023. Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie in his acceptance speech appreciated the leadership of the Uhurie United Union for founding him Worthy of such a highly coveted honour Which he never expected,because he believes in the dignity of labour and the fundamental ethos of adding value to human capital to make society a better place than he met it without recourse to human praise. The elated Youth Ambassador affirmedthat even though he never expected the award, it will definitely spur him to do more for the betterment of his Ughelli South Constituency people when he gets to the House of Assembly by the grace of God. The immediate past governor’s aide , seized the opportunity to appreciate the Road Master Governor, His Excellency, Senator Dr Arthur Ifeanyi Okowa, for bringing him on board to serve as an Aide until very recently when he resigned from the appointment in line with the electoral guidelines to enable him contest for the Ughelli South Constituency seat. POLL Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie who was poised and resolute said: ” I am available for the people of Ughelli South to send to the House,it is my compassionate appeal for all the delegates to support me because as a grassroot politician I will not disappoint them.” Continuing he said: ” lf my popularity rating is anything to go by, to a very large extent I have confidence in the delegates who knows about my political sagacity and ability to attract good things to my Constituency, using the instruments of my good office if elected,by the grace of God, l am certain of victory in the game .” Hon Dr Gordons Okomitie who also appreciated all the elders and Political leaders in Ughelli South for their cooperation so far, also enjoined the Youths, the women and various pressure groups in Ughelli South to continuegiving him their unalloyed support as they have been doing since he announced his intention to contest for the Ughelli South House of Assembly seat.